-- Ireland's NAMA sells loan portfolio to Blackstone
-- By Sam Cage
-- Mon May 12, 2014 10:16AM EDT
-- None



DUBLIN, May 12 (Reuters) - Ireland's "bad bank" sold a portfolio of loans with a par value of 1.8 billion euros ($2.5 billion) to Blackstone Real Estate Partners Europe IV <BX.N>, it said on Monday.

